===Etymology===
  +   +
The name "Google" is a play on the word ''[[googol]]'', which was coined by [[Milton Sirotta]], nephew of [[United States|U.S.]] [[mathematician]] [[Edward Kasner]] in [[1938]], to refer to the number represented by 1 followed by a hundred zeros. Google's use of the term reflects the company's mission to organize the immense amount of information available on the Web. It was coined by [[Andy Bechtolsheim]] who made out a check to "Google Inc."
